# Design System Rules

> **Stack**: Tailwind CSS 3 + HSL CSS variable tokens + shadcn/ui + IBM Plex Sans/Mono
> **Severity levels**: MUST (non-negotiable), SHOULD (strongly recommended), PREFER (polish)

---

## 1. Color Tokens & Theming

### Token Architecture

- MUST: All colors are defined as HSL CSS custom properties in `index.css` (`:root` for light, `.dark` for dark, `.high-contrast` for high contrast). Never use raw hex, rgb, or Tailwind color name classes (e.g., `bg-blue-100`, `text-green-600`) in component code.
- MUST: Use semantic token names in components (`--primary`, `--accent`, `--destructive`, `--success`, `--warning`, `--info`, `--muted`, `--foreground`, `--background`, `--card`, `--border`). Never reference visual color names.
- MUST: The `--accent` token must be visually distinct from `--primary`. Currently both sit in the 207–212° hue range. Accent should be differentiated (recommended: teal/cyan ~180° hue range or as chosen from the approved palettes).
- MUST: The `--info` token must not duplicate `--accent`. These serve different semantic purposes.

### Contrast Requirements

- MUST: `--foreground` on `--background` ≥ 4.5:1.
- MUST: `--muted-foreground` on `--background` ≥ 4.5:1 for normal-size text. Current value is borderline (~4.48:1) — audit and increase lightness separation if needed.
- MUST: `--primary-foreground` on `--primary` ≥ 4.5:1.
- MUST: `--destructive-foreground` on `--destructive` ≥ 4.5:1.
- MUST: `--warning-foreground` on `--warning` in dark mode must not be pure black `0 0% 0%` — use a dark warm tone (e.g., `32 100% 10%`) for better readability.
- MUST: Status colors (success, warning, destructive) on `--card` background must meet 3:1 non-text contrast for badges and icons, and 4.5:1 for text labels.

### Chart Colors

- MUST: No two adjacent chart segments share the same hue family. Chart-1 and Chart-2 must be visually distinguishable in both color and greyscale.
- MUST: Chart colors work in greyscale mode (already designed for this — maintain it).
- SHOULD: Provide pattern fills or distinct shapes as a secondary differentiator alongside color.

### Dark Mode & High Contrast

- MUST: Every new CSS variable added to `:root` must also have a `.dark` and `.high-contrast` variant defined.
- MUST: Dark mode token values are not simply inverted — they are intentionally designed for readability. Maintain minimum contrast ratios in all modes.
- MUST: The `index.html` initial class and `AccessibilityContext` default must be synchronized to prevent flash of incorrect theme (dark → light → dark). Default `darkMode` to `document.documentElement.classList.contains('dark')`.

---

## 2. Typography

- MUST: Use the established font stack — IBM Plex Sans for UI text, IBM Plex Mono for code/data. Never introduce additional font families without design review.
- MUST: All font sizes use `rem` or Tailwind size classes (`text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, etc.). Never set `font-size` in `px` on the root element or via inline styles.
- SHOULD: Body text is 14–16px equivalent (`text-sm` or `text-base`). Data-dense tables may use `text-xs` (12px) but never smaller.
- MUST: Numeric values in stat cards and dashboards use `toLocaleString()` for proper thousand separators and locale-aware formatting.
- SHOULD: Large numeric displays (stat card values) should use tabular-nums (`font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`) for alignment.

---

## 3. Spacing & Layout

### Responsive Padding

- MUST: Main content area uses responsive padding: `p-4 sm:p-6` minimum. Never use fixed `p-6` across all breakpoints.
- SHOULD: Apply `max-w-screen-2xl mx-auto` to the main content area to prevent edge-to-edge text on ultrawide monitors.

### Grid & Breakpoints

- MUST: Platform tab grids (Devices, Profiles) must be responsive. Never use fixed `grid-cols-6` without responsive fallbacks. Use `grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-6` or `flex-wrap`.
- MUST: Dashboard stat card grids use `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4`.
- MUST: All layouts must work from 320px (mobile) to ultrawide without horizontal overflow for vertical-flow content.

### Elevation & Depth

- SHOULD: Cards use subtle shadow on hover (`hover:shadow-md`) with smooth transition (`transition-shadow duration-200`).
- SHOULD: Stat cards have a hover lift effect (`hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-transform`) for interactive feedback.
- SHOULD: Elevated surfaces (header, modals, popovers) use `backdrop-blur-sm` with partial background opacity for glassmorphism depth.
- PREFER: Stat cards use subtle gradient tint based on variant (`from-{variant}/[0.03] to-transparent`) for visual differentiation.

---

## 4. Component Visual Standards

### Cards

- MUST: Use the `.stat-card` design system class for all stat/metric cards. Never build inline card markup with raw `<Card>` when the stat-card pattern exists.
- MUST: Variant differentiation uses the left-border color pattern plus icon color. Never rely on border color alone.
- SHOULD: Loading states use `<Skeleton>` components with `aria-busy="true"` and descriptive `aria-label`.

### Buttons & Interactive Targets

- MUST: All clickable targets are at least 24×24px (WCAG 2.5.8).
- MUST: Primary actions use `--primary` background. Destructive actions use `--destructive`. Secondary/ghost actions use transparent backgrounds.
- SHOULD: Buttons have subtle press feedback (`active:scale-[0.97]` with `transition-transform`).

### Status Badges

- MUST: Badges combine color AND a secondary indicator (icon or text label). Examples: ✓ Compliant (green), ✕ Non-compliant (red), ⏳ Pending (orange).
- MUST: Badge text meets minimum contrast ratio against the badge background.

### Tables (DataTable)

- MUST: Table rows have a hover state (`hover:bg-accent/5` with `transition-colors`).
- MUST: Empty states are illustrated with a message and action, not plain text.
- SHOULD: Loading states use staggered skeleton rows.

---

## 5. Animation & Motion

### General Rules

- MUST: All animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`. When active, disable transforms, slides, and bounces — use instant or opacity-only transitions.
- MUST: Only animate `transform` and `opacity` properties for GPU acceleration. Never animate `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `margin`, or `padding`.
- MUST: No animation exceeds 400ms duration. Page transitions ≤ 250ms. Micro-interactions ≤ 200ms.
- MUST: No content flashes more than 3 times per second.

### Specific Animations

- SHOULD: Page transitions use Framer Motion fade+slide (`opacity` + `translateY`) with `AnimatePresence`.
- SHOULD: Stat card values animate counting up on mount using Framer Motion `useMotionValue`.
- SHOULD: Sidebar active nav item has an animated indicator bar using Framer Motion `layoutId`.
- PREFER: Table rows stagger entry on page load with 50–100ms delay per row.
- PREFER: Notification badge has a subtle pulse when new notifications arrive.

### Library Rules

- MUST: Use Framer Motion (already installed) for orchestrated animations. Do not add GSAP, anime.js, or additional animation libraries.
- MUST: Use CSS transitions for simple hover/focus effects. Reserve Framer Motion for page transitions, staggered lists, layout animations, and counter animations.
- SHOULD: Use Framer Motion's `whileInView` for elements entering the viewport. Do not animate off-screen elements.

---

## 6. Iconography

- MUST: Use Lucide React icons consistently. Do not mix icon libraries.
- MUST: Platform logos (Android, iOS, Windows, macOS, Linux) use consistent sizing and style. Prefer SVG over PNG for platform icons.
- MUST: Decorative icons carry `aria-hidden="true"`. Meaningful icons have an accessible name.
- SHOULD: Icon containers in stat cards and nav items use consistent sizing (`w-5 h-5` for nav, `w-6 h-6` for cards, `w-4 h-4` for inline).

---

## 7. Design Consistency Rules

- MUST: Use design system tokens everywhere. Hardcoded color values (`bg-blue-100`, `text-green-600`, `#636D77`) are forbidden in component files.
- MUST: Use `cn()` utility (from `@/lib/utils`) for conditional class merging. Never string-concatenate Tailwind classes.
- MUST: Components consuming the design system must not define their own color tokens. All color decisions flow from `index.css` variables through `tailwind.config.ts`.
- SHOULD: When a design pattern exists in one page (e.g., `WebApplications.tsx` uses AlertDialog for delete confirmation), all pages must follow the same pattern.
